headline: Stanley Black & Decker’s Q2 Earnings Call: Our Top 5 Analyst Questions
summary: Stanley Black & Decker’s second quarter results were met with a significant negative market reaction, reflecting disappointment around revenue performance and ongoing margin pressures. headline: SWK Q2 Deep Dive: Tariffs and Supply Chain Actions Dominate as Leadership Transition Looms
summary: Manufacturing company Stanley Black & Decker (NYSE:SWK) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales falling 2% year on year to $3.95 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.08 per share was significantly above analysts’ consensus estimates.
